While I do agree with your points, I feel like you got yourself chained to your "format". Why not try something new when talking about those shows?

I think that if you keep recycling your own videos, it's inevitable that you're going to feel creatively burned out... it might be good for you too if you try new things! I know it's probably hard since you feel like you failed with other formats in the past and this one got you so much success; but now that you have so many followers, we can provide you with the feedback you may need to refine it and do it right :)

Don't get me wrong, I really enjoy your videos, and I think you should continue making them! But you know, think about it -- you can shake things up once in a while :)

snippet.textDisplay:
I remember in the late 90's and early 2000s, there was a rash of "teen movies" and then they decided to do a parody called "Not Another Teen Movie" which had a lot of funny scenes parodying "She's All That" and "10 Things I Hate About You", but then they attempted to do a scene that parodies "American Pie" which in and of itself was an absurdist movie, and "Not Another Teen Movie" did it with an over the top diarrhea gag that was so gross it brought the entire movie to a screeching halt and was just awful in an otherwise funny film parody.

So yes I agree. Making fun of comedy does not work.
